[2] Rotavirus - Mexico
Date: Sun 27 Feb 2005
From: ProMED-mail <promed@promedmail.org>
Source: Xinhuanet News Agency, Sat 26 Feb 2005 [edited]
<http://news.xinhuanet.com/english/2005-02/27/content_2624192.htm>

Mexico: suspected rotavirus diarrhea kills 62 children
------------------------------------------------------
At least 62 people, mostly children under 5, have died as a result of
diarrhea caused by rotavirus in Central America, reports here said on
Saturday [26 Feb 2005]. The reports quoted Health Ministries of these
countries as saying that 108 403 cases of diarrhea had been reported
this year [2005] in Central America, with Nicaragua reporting the
highest toll of 32.
Nicaragua had 27 997 confirmed cases of diarrhea until last weekend
[3rd weekend of February 2005], most of which were found in the
northern departments of Madriz and Esteli.
El Salvador, in which the highest number of cases, 73 274, were
reported, maintains a state of emergency, declared on 8 Feb 2005, in
the most affected departments of San Salvador, La Libertad and La
Paz, the reports said. At least 20 people have been killed by the
disease in El Salvador.
Rotavirus had also killed 8 children in Guatemala, where the health
authorities had reported 700 possible cases of the disease, of which
386 had been confirmed.
Honduras has not reported any diarrhea cases this year [2005],
although, in 2004, it reported 236 966 cases, mostly among children
below 5 years of age, the reports said.
--
