[6] Rotavirus - Russia (Ekaterinburg)
Date: Fri 4 Mar 2005
From: Natalia Pchenitchnaia <crane@aaanet.ru>
Source: ITAR-TASS News Agency, Fri 4 Mar 2005 [translated from Russian,
edited]
<http://www.itartass.ur.ru/news/? id=3D84>

Russia: rotavirus outbreak in Ekaterinburg
------------------------------------------
In Ekaterinburg, children's hospitals are working to capacity on
account of an increase in gastroenteritis among children. As many as
15-20 children have been admitted to hospitals daily for several
weeks. According to the City Public Health Department, rotavirus
infection is the most common cause of hospitalization. The majority
of sick children are in the one-to-2 age group. A proportion of
children are in serious condition, because their parents have treated
them at home, and these children exhibited conditions of exicosis and
toxicosis.
According to the Territorial Statistical Department, in the
Sverdlovsk region in the past year [2004], more than 874 000 persons
have been ill with infectious and parasitic illnesses. The largest
gastroenteritis outbreaks have occurred in Irbit, where more than 150
persons, 113 of whom were children, have fallen ill because of the
consumption of poor-quality water. The same situation exists in
Krasnoturyinsk, where the number of patients also was measured in the
hundreds.
[Byline: Yulia Manina]
